President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring December 10, 2020, as Human Rights Day, December 15, 2020, as Bill of Rights Day, and the week beginning on December 6, 2020, as Human Rights Week. The proclamation highlights the importance of the rights and freedoms enshrined in the Declaration of Independence and the Constitution, and their significance in advancing individual human rights around the world. The proclamation also emphasizes the commitment of the United States to fighting human rights abuses and promoting religious freedom internationally. The President calls upon the people of the United States to observe these occasions with appropriate ceremonies and activities.